page.title: 16NORTHEND'S OLDEST RESIDENT
page.content: Mr.and Mrs.Gibbins are the oldest people in Northend.Mr.Gibbins is 89 years old and Mrs.Gibbins is 87 years old.They left school when aged 13. The village has changed a lot during their lives.There are three times as many houses as there were when Mr.Gibbins was a boy.There used to be three cottages in what is now the "Red Lion" car-park.Once the{Prebend}was an allotment but a small housing estate was built there in the 1950s.{Nortons {Close}was a field called 'Nortons Close'. Twelve houses were built there in the 1950s and a few years later they built six more.In the 1960s an orchard,which grew in{Top Street,}was removed and a number of modern houses built.
